headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown and Marcus Smart each scored 24 points, and the Boston Celtics stopped a three-game slide by topping the Phoenix Suns 123-108 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown, Smart star as Celtics beat Suns 123-108

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan made a 28-foot 3-pointer at the buzzer to give the Chicago Bulls a 108-106 victory over the Indiana Pacers on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeMar DeRozan hits 3 at buzzer, Bulls beat Pacers 108-106

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis had 24 points, nine rebounds and six assists to help the Dallas Mavericks roll past the Sacramento Kings 112-96 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis scores 24 to help Mavericks beat Kings 112-96

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler scored a season-high 37 points and the short-handed Miami Heat built a big lead early and held on for a 120-110 win over the Houston Rockets on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler scores season-high 37, Heat beat Rockets 120-110

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 35 points, Clint Capela had 18 points and a season-high 23 rebounds, and the Atlanta Hawks rallied from a 16-point deficit for a 121-118 win over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 35, Hawks rally to beat Cavaliers 121-118

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 25 points and matched his career-high with 19 rebounds, Fred VanVleet scored 31 points and the Toronto Raptors beat the Los Angeles Clippers 116-108 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pascal Siakam scores 25, Raptors beat Clippers 116-108

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 30 points, eight assists and six rebounds, leading the Memphis Grizzlies to a 118-105 victory over the San Antonio Spurs on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant scores 30, Grizzlies beat Spurs for 4th straight win

events.name: New York Knicks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander returned from a one-game absence to score 23 points, and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat a depleted New York Knicks team 95-80 on Friday night.
— Donovan Mitchell scored a season-high 39 points and the Utah Jazz beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 120-108 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz pull away in 4th quarter, beat Timberwolves 120-108

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — One day after quietly celebrating his 37th birthday at home with his family, LeBron James put on an age-defying performance.
headlines.shortLinkText: James scores season-high 43, Lakers beat Trail Blazers
